<p>Hello,</p>
<p>Thank you for asking to connect to GovWifi.</p>
<p>GovWifi is a secure wifi service.<br />You only need to get connected once. You&rsquo;ll then access GovWifi wherever it&rsquo;s available.</p>
<p><strong>Your GovWifi username: %LOGIN%</strong><br /><strong>Your GovWifi password: %PASS%</strong></p>
<p>When you arrive at a government building where GovWifi is available, follow the instructions below for the device you want to connect.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="#android">Android devices</a></li>
<li><a href="#windows8or10">Windows 8 or 10</a></li>
<li><a href="#windows7">Windows 7</a></li>
<li><a href="#iphoneipad">iPhone or iPad</a></li>
<li><a href="#mac">Mac, iMac or Macbook</a></li>
<li><a href="#chromebook">Chromebook</a></li>
</ul>
<p>By connecting to GovWifi, you agree to the terms and conditions:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gov.uk/govwifi">https://www.gov.uk/govwifi</a></p>


<h1 id="android">Android devices:</h1>
<ol>
<li>Open your wifi settings. A list of wifi networks appears.</li>
<li>Select <strong>GovWifi</strong>. A settings menu appears.</li>
<li>For <strong>EAP method</strong>, select <strong>PEAP</strong>.</li>
<li>For <strong>Phase 2 authentication</strong>, select <strong>MSCHAPV2</strong>.</li>
<li>For <strong>CA Certificate</strong>, ensure that <strong>(unspecified)</strong> or <strong>Do not check</strong> is selected.</li>
<li>If your device asks for your <strong>Domain</strong>, enter&nbsp;<strong>wifi.service.gov.uk</strong></li>
<li>For <strong>Identity</strong>, enter your GovWifi&nbsp;username.</li>
<li>Leave <strong>Anonymous identity</strong> blank.</li>
<li>For <strong>Password</strong>, enter your GovWifi&nbsp;password.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Connect</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<p>Having problems connecting? Contact the helpdesk in your building.</p>


<h1 id="windows8or10">Windows 8 or 10:</h1>
<ol>
<li>Select the wifi icon in the system tray at the bottom right of your screen. You will see all the nearby wifi networks.</li>
<li>Select <strong>GovWifi</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Connect</strong>.</li>
<li>If it says can&rsquo;t <strong>connect to network</strong>, your device may have an incorrect or expired username and password for GovWifi. To fix this issue, tell your device to forget this connection, and then try again.</li>
<li>Enter your GovWifi&nbsp;username and password.</li>
<li>Select <strong>OK</strong>.</li>
<li>When you see <strong>Continue connecting</strong>, select <strong>Show certificate details</strong>.</li>
<li>Check that the <strong>Server thumbprint</strong> matches: %THUMBPRINT%</li>
<li>If it matches, select <strong>Connect</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<p>Having problems connecting? Contact the helpdesk in your building.</p>


<h1  id="windows7">Windows 7:</h1>
<p>Open the <strong>Control Panel</strong>, and select <strong>Network and Sharing Center</strong>.</p>
<ol>
<li>Select <strong>Set up a new connection or network</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Manually connect to a wireless network</strong>.</li>
<li>For the <strong>Network name</strong>, enter <strong>GovWifi</strong> and for the <strong>Security type</strong>, select <strong>WPA2-Enterprise</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Next</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Change connection settings</strong>.</li>
<li>Select the <strong>Security</strong> tab and select <strong>Settings</strong>.</li>
<li>Tick the <strong>Connect to these servers</strong> box. In the text box below it, enter <strong>wifi.service.gov.uk</strong></li>
<li>In the <strong>Trusted Root Certification Authorities</strong> list, select <strong>GeoTrust Primary Certification Authority - G3</strong>.</li>
<li>Tick <strong>Enable Identity Privacy</strong> and enter <strong>anonymous</strong> to prevent your device from broadcasting your username whenever it connects.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Configure</strong>.</li>
<li>Untick <strong>Automatically use my Windows logon name</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>OK</strong>, then <strong>OK</strong> again to go back to the <strong>GovWifi Wireless Network Properties</strong> window.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Advanced settings</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>User authentication</strong> from the dropdown menu under <strong>Specify authentication mode</strong>, then select <strong>Save credentials</strong>.</li>
<li>Enter your GovWifi username and password.</li>
<li>Select <strong>OK</strong> to close all windows.</li>
<li>Select the wifi logo at the bottom right of your screen and select <strong>GovWifi</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<p>Having problems connecting? Contact the helpdesk in your building.</p>


<h1  id="iphoneipad">iPhone or iPad:</h1>
<ol>
<li>Go to wifi settings and select <strong>GovWifi</strong>.</li>
<li>Enter your GovWifi&nbsp;username and password.</li>
<li>You&rsquo;ll be asked to confirm that the network presents the correct certificate. This protects you against fake networks which may harm your privacy.<br />The correct certificate is&nbsp;called <strong>wifi.service.gov.uk</strong> and is issued by <strong>GeoTrust DV SSL SHA256 CA</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>More Details</strong>.</li>
<li>Check that&nbsp;the key identifier matches <strong>49 ec a7 c8 a9 f7 c5 bb 2c aa 24 e7 f4 43 b3 b1 3c e8 54 f8</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Certificate</strong> in the top left to go back to the previous screen.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Trust</strong> in the top right to connect to GovWifi.</li>
</ol>
<p>Having problems connecting? Contact the helpdesk in your building.</p>


<h1  id="mac">Mac, iMac or Macbook:</h1>
<ol>
<li>Select the wifi symbol on the top right of your screen.</li>
<li>Select <strong>GovWifi</strong>.</li>
<li>Enter your GovWifi&nbsp;username and password.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Join</strong>. You will be asked to confirm the network is not a fake by checking the certificate.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Show Certificate</strong>.</li>
<li>Check&nbsp;that the certificate is called <strong>wifi.service.gov.uk</strong> and it&rsquo;s issued by the <strong>GeoTrust DV SSL SHA256 CA</strong>.</li>
<li>If so, select <strong>Continue</strong>.</li>
<li>Your device will ask you for your computer password to save these settings. This is the password you normally use to sign into your computer.</li>
</ol>
<p>Having problems connecting? Contact the helpdesk in your building.</p>


<h1 id="chromebook">Chromebook:</h1>
<ol>
<li>Select the wireless symbol in the bottom right of the screen. A list of wifi connections appears.</li>
<li>Select <strong>GovWifi</strong>. A settings menu appears.</li>
<li>For <strong>EAP method</strong>, select <strong>PEAP</strong>.</li>
<li>For <strong>Phase-2 authentication</strong>, select <strong>MSCHAPV2</strong>.</li>
<li>For <strong>Server CA certificate</strong>, select <strong>Default</strong>.</li>
<li>For <strong>Identity</strong>, enter your GovWifi&nbsp;username.</li>
<li>For <strong>Password</strong>, enter your GovWifi&nbsp;password.</li>
<li>Leave <strong>Anonymous identity</strong> blank.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Connect</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<p>Having problems connecting? Contact the helpdesk in your building.</p>